SIMPLE: epichordal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epichordal
<hw>Ep`i*chor"dal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + <ets>chordal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Upon or above the notochord; -- applied esp. to a vertebral column
which develops upon the dorsal side of the notochord, as distinguished
from a <contr>perichordal</contr> column, which develops around
it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epichorial</ent>⟦br⟧
